{"/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_anaconda_ver01/data/sn85053044/00517178135/1949052701/0164.xml":{"full_text":"THE BROWNING CHIEF\nJohn E. Davies, Editor and Owner\nA weekly newspaper published\nevery Friday at Browning, Glacier\nCounty, Montana.\nEntered as 2nd class matter July 15.\n1931 at the postoffice at Browning,\nMontana, under act of March 3, 1879.\nSubscription $2.00 year in advance\nFACING FISCAL FACTS\nNeither President Truman nor\nCongress is facing up to the act\nual financial position of the United\nStates.\nThe President has just declared\nthat he stands on his January\nproposal for $4,000,000,000 in new\ntaxes. In his pre s s conference\nMr. Truman put the emphasis on\ndebt payments, and at first only\nsaid that the amount of taxes\nwould depend on \"how things\nworked out.\u2019\u2019 But when pressed\nhe refused to retreat from the\n$4,000,000,000 figure. In doing so\nit seems to us he fails to recognize\nthe danger in piling on taxes at\na time when business is declin\ning. His own economic advisers\nare reported in favor of some tax\ncuts.\nFor its part. Congress blithely\ngoes ahead adding to the costs of\ngovernment. The Senate has just\nvoted a $3,000,000,000 appropria\ntions bill for the Treasury and\nPost Office, not merely rejecting\npleas for a 5 per cent reduction\nbut actually tacking on $40,000,-\n000 more than the House had ap\nproved. A couple of weeks ago\nthe House added more than a\nbillion to the bill for armed ser\nvices. In all this it seems to us\nCongress is failing to recognize\nthe danger of an unbalanced bud\nget.\nFor federal expenses are being\npushed up at the very time fed\neral revenues are declining. And\neven without Congress \u201cbuying\u201d\nany hew spending projects costs\nare mounting. The decline in\nfarm prices adds to the bill for\nsupporting farm prices. Slower\nbusiness is sending more service\nmen back to college\u2014and lifting\nthe expected bill for GI benefits.\nThe cost of arming America\u2019s\nallies is likely to r u n to another\nbillion.\nIt may be that Mr. Truman is\nnot looking backward to inflation\ndays in sticking to his tax plan,\nbut rather looking ahead to defla\ntion days. He may have advance\nnotice that tax returns are not\ncoming up to estimates for this\nyear, and that next year\u2019s rev\nenues will be sharply down. We\nPlumbing Electric Service\nIs the Place to Buy\nTABLE MODEL\nG. E. Radios 18 95\nWARING\nSteam Irons... *19 95\nG. E. Vacuums 59 95\nSUNBEAM\nCoHemasters 29 50\nSUNBEAM\nMixmasters 39 75\nSunbeam Attachments 1.18 up\nWe Have a Wide Setectioa if\nNationally Advertized AppHaaces.\nPlumbing Wiring Heating\nBROWNING HUGO CLAPP\n18-R Service of Course\nThis Spring... it seems everybody's fancy is turning to /J 2\nof a//\nTte riMUw O\u00bb U\u00bb 4-Ow Man\nVkib ogUwwl .1 Mtr. tori.\nand tAe reason is,\nitgives so mucA and costs so iitt/e to operate and maintain\nIVIOSf Yes, S 0 g s for new Chevrolets this\ni _ spring that it seems everybody's fancy is turning to\nBoCUtifui BUY for\u2014 thi S most beautiful buy of all!\nSTYLING All America is thrilling to the fleet, flashing lines\nand colors of Chevrolet\u2019s Bodies by Fisher to\nDRIVING AND the sparkling and spirited performance of its Valve-\nRIDING EASE in-Head Engine ami to the extraordinary new\ndriving and riding results imparled by its famous\nCOMFORT Center-Point Design. And all America is agreeing\nAH.ROUND SAFETY that Chevrolet is the only car that offers all these\nadvantages of highest-priced cars and costs so little\nTHRILLS AND THRIFT to buy, operate and maintain!\nHUT FOB QUALITY AT LOWEST COST <4!| ITSutf AMERICA'S CHOICE FOR 1t YEARS\nI\nShurr Chevrolet, Browning, Montana\nwould agree with h i s insistence\nthat in normal times Americans\nshould continue to cut a national\ndebt which runs to a quarter of a\ntrillion dollars. But we wish he\nwould put economy ahead of taxes\nas a way to do it.\nThe Hoover Commission has\ngiven Congress a blueprint for\nsaving $3,000,000,000. Let Presi\ndent and Congress face the fiscal\nfacts and set this saving as the\nfirst step toward balancing the\nbudget\nIt the business recession should\ncontinue and unemployment\ngrow, Congress would almost\nsurely launch a big public works\nprogram. To be effective, this\nTHE BROWNING CHIEF\nwould require a large increase in\nthe debt. The very possibility of\nsuch emergency action under\nscores the need for tightening\nthe nation\u2019s fiscal belt at this\ntime. To launch into deficit fi\nnancing in a period of prosperity\nwould be a plain confession that\nfederal finances were out of cor\ntrol. More, it wbuld announce\nthat the American people were\nmorally and politically bankrupt.\n\u2014Christian Science Monitor.\nGuardipee Attends\nResourse Group\nEvent In North Idaho\nAttending as a member of the\nresource group, Francis X. Guard\nipee, who returned early this\nweek, said that the Northwest\nRecreation Laboratory held at\nCamp Chatcolet, near Plummer,\nIdaho, was a most constructive\nevent.\nIt was not sponsored by any\nparticular group, the people at\ntending being of tn e several re\nligious denominations and rep\nresenting the various walks of\nlife\u2014Extension Service, Farmer\u2019s\nUnion, youth groups, 4-H Clubs,\netc.\nThe object of the meeting was\nto get leaders to bring to adult\ngroups all phases of recreation,\nsinging in groups, song leading,\ncrafts in leather and metal, or\nanything else that might be of\nvalue to anyone in any com\nmunity.\nCeremonials of all kinds were\nenjoyed by all and everyone had\nan opportunity to lead or take\npart in the activities. No one was\nobliged to do anything except to\nbe friendly and to enjoy them\nselves.\nOld time dances were o n eof\nthe features, square dance call\ning was one of the most import\nant items for study, speaking be\nfore people was also studied,\ngames for old and young, family\nand community group singing,\nnature study and swimming.\nIt is planned to hold the next\nsession at th e same place next\nyear with a change to some other\nsection the following year.\nmajority of those attending this\ntime were from Montana but all\nnorthwest states were represent\ned. The plan is to reactivate an\ninterest in old time dancing, folk\nsinging and anything that may\nbe useful in community recrea\ntion.\nAwards Presented\n(Continued from first page)\nAgriculturr, district convention\n\u2014Jack Wood, farm shop, first;\nI livestock, third; Jack Powell, sec\nond; livestock team, Eugene\nKipp. Jack Wood, Jerry Show,\nsecond; farm shop team, Robert\nPowell, Gordon Grayson, Jack\nWood; chapter secretary, Lee\nWilson, bronze award; treasurer,\nKenneth Juneau, silver award;\nfarm improvement, Robert Mad\nman, silver division; chapter\nscrapbook, gold divsion; chapter\nreporter, Dennis Harris, gold di\nvision; chapter emblem awards,\nJack Wood, Jerry Show, Eugene\nKipp, Dennis Harris, Lee Wilson.\nKenneth Juneau, Robert Powell,\nJohn Powell, Gordon Grayson,\nRobert Madman, Wayne Racine,\nEd Conway, Fred Pambrun; pub\nlic speaking, Jack Wood; fresh\nman project award, John Powell.\nHeisey awards, SSO each\u2014Cora\nPambrun, Mae Boyd, Margaret\nMcKay, Earl Old Person.\nDon Hagerty award \u2014Earl Old\nPerson.\nBICYCLE\nREPAIRING\nLet Us Repair Your Bicycle,\nTricycle, Guns, Gas Washing\nMachine Motors, Etc.\nCOMPLETE LINE OF\nBICYCLE REPAIR\nPARTS IN STOCK\nBrowning Furniture\nExchange\n(Second Hand Store)\nPhone 87-W\nyou\u2019ll v\" z I\nHSVEK\nus sonny x\nyou sn ved ka fr\n1 I\nArgue as you will about high prices .11 j|\ninflation good times bemg here for\never this we know You\u2019ll Never Be\nSorry You Saved. You\u2019ll forget the sac\nrifices you made it won\u2019t matter\nwhether good times stay or not... you\u2019ll\nhave money m the bank, and that\u2019s\nAlways something to be thankful fort\nThe First National Bank\nof Browning\nDesignated Depository of Indian Funds\nMember Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation II\nAT THIS BANK\nn 1 BATTERIES\nRadio K b r e t s s\nREPAIR WORK DONE ON ALL MAKES\nOF HOME AND AUTO RADIOS, PHONE\nGRAPHS AND COMBINATIONS.\nRADIO ELECTRIC\nE. T. BROOKS [PHONE 111\nCOME TO\nThe Rocky Mt. Inn\nAND HAVE FUN\nDancing Every Night\nSpecial Music Every Weekend.\nHamby\u2019s\nService Sia.\nPHONE 85\nAlways at Your Service\nOur Shop Phone\nNumber 79-M\nOval E Station\nReservation Women Picked\nUp On Morals Charge\nThe Chief this week was in\nreceipt of a clipping from a Top\npenish, Wash., newspaper bear\ning a story involving three Res\nervation women, Mildred Cut\nFinger, 21; Marie Mae Cut Fin\nger, 19, and Florence Morning\nGun. 19. The three were a group\nof five charged with prostitution.\nThey were taken before a justice\nof the peace and given a term of\nsix months in the county jail.\nHowever, he proposed the alter\nnative of getting out of the state\nof Washington, and remaining\nout for three years.\nDelivers Junior High Address\nFrancis X. Guardipee delivered\nthe annual commencement ad\ndress to students of the Cascade\nJunior high school Tuesday even\ning, his subject being Education.\nAdvertising Pays","height":"20408","width":"14784"}}
